returns._0: Result True if calls to all targets returned True. Otherwise, false
Result True if `maker` has specified epoch. Otherwise, false
Result True if call to target returns the same value as `value`. Otherwise, false
Result True if call to target returns value which is bigger than `value`. Otherwise, false
Result True if call to target returns value which is lower than `value`. Otherwise, false
Result True if call to target returns 0. Otherwise, false
Result True if call to any target returned True. Otherwise, false

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

params.action: The data representing the action to be executed after the permit.
params.permit: ERC20 token address (20 bytes) concatenated with the permit data, allowing this contract to spend the token. Format: [token address (20 bytes)][permit data]

and(uint256,bytes).notice: Calls every target with corresponding data

arbitraryStaticCall(address,bytes).notice: Performs an arbitrary call to target with data

eq(uint256,bytes).notice: Calls target with specified data and tests if it's equal to the value

gt(uint256,bytes).notice: Calls target with specified data and tests if it's bigger than value

lt(uint256,bytes).notice: Calls target with specified data and tests if it's lower than value

not(bytes).notice: Calls target with specified data and tests if it's equal to 0

or(uint256,bytes).notice: Calls every target with corresponding data

permitAndCall(bytes,bytes).notice: Executes a permit for an ERC20 token and then a specified action in a single transaction.
